  "prompt": "How do you pronounce \"L\"?",
  "response": "The letter \"L\" is typically pronounced by placing the tip of the tongue against the ridge behind the upper front teeth (called the alveolar ridge) and releasing air around the sides of the tongue. There are two main variants:\n\n1. Light \"L\" (like in \"light\" or \"love\"): The tongue tip touches the alveolar ridge, creating a clear, crisp sound.\n\n2. Dark \"L\" (like in \"full\" or \"milk\"): The back of the tongue is raised slightly, creating a slightly different sound.\n\nThe pronunciation can vary slightly depending on the language and specific context.",
